Naivasha residents have said they have been locked out of the preparations for the 4th Annual Devolution Conference.The meeting starts today at the Kenya Wildlife Service Training Institute, Nakuru county. Major roads leading to the institute were closed off and only visitors going to the conference were allowed through. Naivasha Professionals Association chairman Absolom Mukuusi said residents were not involved. &ldquo;We have come to learn that only those invited can get access to the venue and we are wondering how the locals will benefit from the conference,&rdquo; he said.He urged the organisers to consider giving a chance to some of the youths, who would like to showcase their talents.Nominated Senator Paul Njoroge said the conference would improve the economy of the town. He denied residents had been locked out, saying the registration was done online.